info.author: Ian Bicking
info.description:
This package provides a Paste interface to Trac (specifically to the
WSGI branch of Trac).  It makes it deployable with Paste, including
new-project setup.  This is in the very early stages, so expect
problems (but also `report them
<http://pythonpaste.org/trac/newticket?summary=TracPaste>`_!).

This project is only installable from the `Subversion repository
<http://svn.pythonpaste.org/Paste/TracPaste/trunk#egg=TracPaste-dev>`_
or with ``easy_install TracPaste==dev``.

Trac must be installed from the `WSGI branch
<http://svn.edgewall.com/repos/trac/sandbox/wsgi#egg=Trac-wsgi>`_ or
as an automatically acquired dependency of this package.
info.name: TracPaste
info.summary: An adaptation of Trac to Paste
info.html_description:
This package provides a Paste interface to Trac (specifically to the WSGI branch of Trac). It makes it deployable with Paste, including new-project setup. This is in the very early stages, so expect problems (but also report them!).

This project is only installable from the Subversion repository or with easy_install TracPaste==dev.

Trac must be installed from the WSGI branch or as an automatically acquired dependency of this package.
